.TH ipmipower.conf 5 "@ISODATE@" "ipmipower @PACKAGE_VERSION@" "System Commands"
.SH "NAME"
ipmipower.conf \- specify alternate default values to ipmipower
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The 
.B ipmipower 
configuration file can be used to set default values to
.B ipmipower 
when values aren't set on the command line.  This allows users to
avoid typing in a long list of command line options everytime
.B ipmipower 
is executed.  It can also be used to hide usernames and passwords from
the
.B ps(1) 
command (See KNOWN ISSUES
in 
.B ipmipower(1) 
for details).

By default, the configuration file is stored at
@IPMIPOWER_CONFIG_FILE_DEFAULT@.  But users may select a different
configuration file at the command line through the --config option.

The user can still override the configuration file values by
specifying the options on the command line.  The configuration file
does not stop a user from specifying any options on the command line.

.SH "CONFIGURATION OPTIONS"
The following are a list of configuration options that can be
specified in the configuration file.  Each configuration option must
be listed on a separate line.  Arguments for an option are separated
by any amount of whitespace.  Multiple arguments are also separated by
whitespace.  Comments can be marked by using the pound sign ("#")
character, and lines can be continued on the next using backslash
("\\").

Note that it is possible to list the username and password in the
configuration file.  If this data is stored in a configuration file,
system administrators should limit access to this file.
.TP
.I hostname host1 host2 host3 ...
Specify the default hostname(s).  Multiple hostnames or hostname ranges
can be specified by separating each range by whitespace.  See
.B ipmipower (1)
for information on hostname ranges.  For example, any of the following
configuration listings would be acceptable:

hostname host1 host2 host3 foo1 bar1

hostname host1,host2,host3,foo1,bar1

hostname host[1-3] foo1 bar1

hostname host[1-3] foo1,bar1

At most 64 hostnames or hostname ranges can be separted by whitespace. 
.TP
.I username str
Specify the default username to use.
.TP
.I password str
Specify the default password to use.
.TP
.I k_g str
Specify the BMC key (K_g) to use.  Prefix the string with '0x' to
specify the key in hexadecimal.
.TP
.I authentication-type str
Specify the default authentication type to use.  
.B Ipmipower 
currently supports the following authentication types:
"auto", "none", "straight_password_key", "md2", and "md5".
.TP
.I privilege str
Specify the default privilege type to use.  
.B Ipmipower 
currently supports the following privilege types: "auto", "user",
"operator", and "admin".
.TP
.I ipmi-version str
Specify the default IPMI protocol version to use: "auto", "1.5", and "2.0"
.TP
.I cipher-suite-id str
Specify the default Cipher Suite ID to use: "auto", "0", "1", "2", "3", "6", "7", "8", "11", 12"
.TP
.I on-if-off enable|disable
Specify if on-if-off is enabled or disabled by default.
.TP
.I wait-until-on enable|disable
Specify if wait-until-on is enabled or disabled by default.
.TP
.I wait-until-off enable|disable
Specify if wait-until-off is enabled or disabled by default.
.TP
.I consolidate-output enable|disable
Specify if consolidate-output is enabled or disabled by default.
.TP
.I eliminate enable|disable
Specify if eliminate is enabled or disabled by default.
.TP
.I workaround-flags str
Specify default workaround flags to use.  See 
.B ipmipower(8)
for list of workarounds that can be specified.
.TP
.I session-timeout ms
Specify the timeout in ms.
.TP
.I retry-timeout ms
Specify the retry timeout in ms.  See
.B ipmipower (1)
for an explanation on the difference between this is the timeout option.
.TP
.I retry-wait-timeout ms
Specify the retry wait timeout in ms.  See
.B ipmipower (1)
for an explanation on the difference between this is the above timeout
options.
.TP
.I retry-backoff-count num
Specify the retry backoff count
.TP 
.I ping-interval ms
Specify the ping interval length in ms.
.TP
.I ping-timeout ms
Specify the ping timeout length in ms.
.TP
.I ping-packet-count num
Specify a new ping packet count
.TP
.I ping-percent num
Specify a new ping percent
.TP
.I ping-consec-count num
Specify a new ping consec count
.LP
.br
.SH "FILES"
@IPMIPOWER_CONFIG_FILE_DEFAULT@
.SH "SEE ALSO"
ipmipower(8)
